{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_31","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.pekko:pekko-slf4j_2.13:1.6.0`. Preserved work is available on https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-5373-library-new-request-org.apache.pekko-pekko-slf4j_2.13-1.6.0-b3ea44ad\n\nDespite the `test_generation_failed` reason, the run got past test generation. The most likely failing stage is post-generation metadata repair / native test execution: the generated Scala test is library-specific, JVM tests pass (`tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-slf4j_2.13/1.6.0/build/test-results/test/TEST-org_apache_pekko.pekko_slf4j_2_13.Pekko_slf4j_2_13Test.xml` shows 6/6 passing), but native execution still fails in the three `ActorSystem`-backed tests. Earlier native runs failed with `ConfigException$Missing: No configuration setting found for key 'pekko.logging-filter'` in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-slf4j_2.13:1.6.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-06T14-44-15-108185Z.log`, and the last preserved native run progressed further but still failed with `ClassNotFoundException: org.apache.pekko.serialization.DisabledJavaSerializer` in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-slf4j_2.13:1.6.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-06T15-09-07-351011Z.log`. The metadata-fix transcript also shows an intermediate unresolved `SerializationExtension$` reachability gap in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-slf4j_2.13:1.6.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`. This points to incomplete Pekko ActorSystem/serialization/default-config reachability metadata rather than a scaffold-only test issue. Dynamic-access coverage is not usable here: `tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-slf4j_2.13/1.6.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json` reports `0/0`, and `stats/org.apache.pekko/pekko-slf4j_2.13/1.6.0/execution-metrics.json` ends with status `failure`.\n\nPlease inspect:\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-slf4j_2.13:1.6.0/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-06T15-09-07-351011Z.log`\n- `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.pekko:pekko-slf4j_2.13:1.6.0/metadata-fix/codex.log`\n- `post-gen-interventions/org.apache.pekko_pekko-slf4j_2.13_1.6.0.md`\n- `tests/src/org.apache.pekko/pekko-slf4j_2.13/1.6.0/test-results-native/test/TEST-junit-jupiter.xml`\n\nNext steps:\n1. Reproduce `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.pekko:pekko-slf4j_2.13:1.6.0` on the preserved branch and focus on the three native `ActorSystem` failures.\n2. Continue the Pekko metadata fix in `metadata/org.apache.pekko/pekko-slf4j_2.13/1.6.0/reachability-metadata.json`, especially around default config resources, `SerializationExtension$`, and `DisabledJavaSerializer`.\n3. Rerun the target library tests after the metadata update and keep the generated ActorSystem tests unless they are replaced with equally library-specific native-safe coverage."}}
